  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 24 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 4 critical, 16 high, 6 medium, 13 normal. Key bases needing attention include Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF); plus 17 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD), Modlin (WMI/EPMO) and Vilnius (VNO/EYVI). Network hotspots: Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Falcone–Borsellino (PMO/LICJ), Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB), Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH) and 19 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, very low visibility and fog / freezing fog. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Josep Tarradellas Barcelona-El Prat (BCN/LEBL), Falcone–Borsellino (PMO/LICJ), Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH) and 9 others.",
